{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund training facilities for jobs you can\u2019t train in college for",
        "additional_details": "I\u2019ve been a chef most of my life and it is impossible to achieve or even come close to being successful at even an interview for any one of these roles given I have zero experience. Funding new training facilities could give not just thousands, but hundreds of thousands a chance to gain a new experience that will then give them the opportunity to start a new career. This could help get people off of the universal credit system and into work.",
        "background": "Create colleges for anyone aged over 16 to provide training for jobs such as forklifting, till operating, bartender, painting and many more that colleges these days cannot provide.",
